        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 24 at 1:42PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 142 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bloys Camp, or 15 miles west of Fort Davis, moving northeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Davis, Bloys Camp, McDonald Observatory, Davis Mountains State
Park, Black Mountain, Buffalo Trail Scout Camp, Indian Lodge, and
Fort Davis National Historical Site.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 PM CDT for
southwestern Texas.</instruction>
